content: Singaporean swimmer (born 1992) **Roanne Ho** (born 27 October 1992) is a retired [Singaporean](/wiki/Singapore) swimmer. In 2018, she won the silver medal in the [women's 50 metre breaststroke](/wiki/Swimming_at_the_2018_Asian_Games_%E2%80%93_Women%27s_50_metre_breaststroke) event at the [2018 Asian Games](/wiki/2018_Asian_Games) held in Jakarta, Indonesia. She also competed in the [women's 100 metre breaststroke](/wiki/Swimming_at_the_2018_Asian_Games_%E2%80%93_Women%27s_100_metre_breaststroke) event. In 2018, she also competed in the [women's 50 metre breaststroke](/wiki/Swimming_at_the_2018_Commonwealth_Games_%E2%80%93_Women%27s_50_metre_breaststroke) and [women's 100 metre breaststroke](/wiki/Swimming_at_the_2018_Commonwealth_Games_%E2%80%93_Women%27s_100_metre_breaststroke) events at the [2018 Commonwealth Games](/wiki/2018_Commonwealth_Games) held in Gold Coast, Australia. She announced her retirement from competitive swimming in February 2019. This biographical article related to a Singaporean swimmer is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it. - v - t - e
title: Roanne Ho
